questions.statement:
&lt;p&gt;Consider the following statements:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;1.&amp;nbsp;Farmers Innovation Fund is a system to scientifically validate, scale up and propagate the innovations of progressive farmers.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;2. ICAR has developed 45 different organic farming models suitable for different agro-climatic regions and has validated 51 integrated farming systems to help increase farm income.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;3. ICAR is developing nano fertilizers and nano pesticides to promote organic farming and to reduce the use of pesticides and fertilizers&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;4. A programme named Arya is also being implemented to improve rural bio-economy and attract youth to agriculture.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Which of the above statement are correct?&lt;/p&gt;

questions.explanation:
&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is&amp;nbsp;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;1, 2, 3, and 4&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Some key initiatives of ICAR:&lt;/strong&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Farmers Innovation Fund&lt;/strong&gt;:

		&lt;ul&gt;
			&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;ICAR is all set to start a system to scientifically validate, scale-up and propagate the innovations of progressive farmers. Hence, Statement 1 is correct.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
			&lt;li&gt;The system intends to link farmers and farming with science and encourage farmers to continue their innovations.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;/ul&gt;
		&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Organic Farming&lt;/strong&gt;
		&lt;ul&gt;
			&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;​ICAR has developed 45 different organic farming models&lt;/strong&gt; suitable for different agro-climatic regions and has validated 51 integrated farming systems to help increase farm income.&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Hence, Statement 2&amp;nbsp;is correct.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;/ul&gt;
		&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Nano fertilizers and Nano pesticides&lt;/strong&gt;
		&lt;ul&gt;
			&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;​ICAR is developing nano fertilizers and nano pesticides &lt;/strong&gt;to promote organic farming and to reduce the use of pesticides and fertilizers.&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Hence, Statement 3&amp;nbsp;is correct.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;/ul&gt;
		&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Attracting and Retaining Youth in Agriculture (Arya)&lt;/strong&gt;
		&lt;ul&gt;
			&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;​A program named Arya is also being implemented to improve rural bio-economy and attract youth to agriculture.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Hence, Statement 4&amp;nbsp;is correct.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;/ul&gt;
		&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Farmers&amp;rsquo; Science Congress&lt;/strong&gt;
		&lt;ul&gt;
			&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;​&lt;/strong&gt;It was inaugurated in 2020 for the first time in the 107 years of history of the Indian Science Congress highlighting the importance of farmers&amp;rsquo; innovations and their scientific validity.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;/ul&gt;
		&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;Future targets:&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span id=&quot;cke_bm_10145S&quot; style=&quot;display: none;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;To ensure that the&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;Pusa Institute (IARI) gets upgraded&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;from a national institute to an institute of international status.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;There is a&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;need to reduce dependence on imports&lt;/strong&gt;, increase the production of healthy foods and also increase the production of pulses and oilseeds.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Palm oil production&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;needs to be increased by research and increased cultivation and development of new varieties of oilseeds need to be emphasized.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The near self-sufficiency achieved in&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;pulses production needs to be replicated&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;for oilseeds production also so that import of edible oils is reduced.&lt;span id=&quot;cke_bm_10145E&quot; style=&quot;display: none;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The correct answer is - Cyclical unemployment&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Cyclical unemployment&lt;/strong&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Cyclical unemployment refers to the deviation of unemployment from its natural rate due to changes in the business cycle.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;It typically arises when there is a downturn in economic activity, such as during a recession, leading to reduced demand for goods and services.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;During such periods, businesses cut back on production and may lay off workers, increasing unemployment rates.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Conversely, during periods of economic expansion, cyclical unemployment decreases as demand for goods and services rises, leading to job creation.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Unlike other types of unemployment, cyclical unemployment is directly tied to macroeconomic conditions and policies.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Nominal rate of unemployment&lt;/strong&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The nominal rate of unemployment refers to the measured rate of unemployment, which includes all types of unemployment but does not specifically address deviations from the natural rate.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;This term does not differentiate between structural, frictional, or cyclical unemployment.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Frictional unemployment&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Frictional unemployment occurs when workers are transitioning between jobs or entering the workforce for the first time.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;It is considered a natural form of unemployment that exists even in a healthy economy.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;This type of unemployment is not caused by economic downturns or business cycles.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Fluctuating unemployment&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Fluctuating unemployment is not a standard term in economics and may refer to variations in unemployment rates over time.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;It does not specifically address the concept of deviations from the natural rate of unemployment.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;J Curve Theory&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;J Curve Theory&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;​J curve theory explains the effect of devaluation on balance of trade.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;A J Curve is an economic theory that states that,&lt;strong&gt; under certain conditions, a country&amp;#39;s trade deficit will initially worsen after its currency depreciates&lt;/strong&gt;, mostly because higher import prices will have a greater influence on total nominal imports in the near term than the reduced number of imports.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The nominal trade deficit initially grows after a devaluation, as prices of exports rise before quantities can adjust.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Then, as quantities adjust, there is an increase in imports as exports remain static, and the trade deficit shrinks or reverses into a surplus forming a &amp;ldquo;J&amp;rdquo; shape.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Apart from trade deficits, the J Curve idea can be applied to other fields such as private equity, medicine, and politics.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/important-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Important Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;img alt=&quot;&quot; src=&quot;//storage.googleapis.com/tb-img/production/22/06/625404ac15b205e629af9c39_16557984135721.png&quot; style=&quot;height: 256px; width: 330px;&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The correct answer is - Unemployment rate = \(\frac{\text { Number of unemployed }}{\text { No. of employed }+\ \rm No.\ of \ unemployed} \times 100\)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Unemployment Rate Formula&lt;/strong&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The unemployment rate is a measure of the percentage of the labor force that is unemployed and actively seeking employment.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The formula for calculating the unemployment rate is: \(\frac{\text { Number of unemployed }}{\text { No. of employed }+\ \rm No.\ of \ unemployed} \times 100\).&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;This formula calculates the proportion of unemployed individuals relative to the total labor force.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The labor force consists of both employed individuals and those actively seeking employment (unemployed).&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Importance of the Unemployment Rate&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The unemployment rate is a crucial indicator of economic health and labor market conditions.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;A high unemployment rate signifies economic challenges and indicates that many individuals are unable to find jobs despite actively seeking work.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;liit and=&quot;&quot; design=&quot;&quot; efficiency=&quot;&quot; evaluate=&quot;&quot; helps=&quot;&quot; labor=&quot;&quot; li=&quot;&quot; market=&quot;&quot; policies=&quot;&quot; policymakers=&quot;&quot; reduce=&quot;&quot; to=&quot;&quot;&gt; &lt;/liit&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Labor Force&lt;/strong&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The labor force includes all individuals who are either employed or actively seeking employment.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;It does not include individuals who are not seeking employment, such as retirees, students, or homemakers.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The labor force is a subset of the adult population, excluding those not participating in economic activities.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Unemployed Individuals&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Unemployed individuals are those who are not currently employed but are actively looking for work.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;They must meet specific criteria, such as being available to start work and actively seeking employment, to be counted as unemployed.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Adult Population&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The adult population typically refers to individuals above a certain age threshold, often 15 or 16 years, depending on the country.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;This population includes both participants in the labor force (employed and unemployed) and non-participants (retirees, students, homemakers, etc.).&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

