questions.explanation:
&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;A) 2, B) 3, C) 1, D) 4&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;P.M. Jan Arogya Abhiyan&lt;/strong&gt;:

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Pradhan Mantri Jan Arogya Yojana&lt;/strong&gt; (PMJAY&lt;strong&gt;)&lt;/strong&gt; to protect poor and vulnerable families against financial risk arising out of catastrophic health episodes.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;ILfuVd&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;hgKElc&quot;&gt;This scheme was launched on 23rd September, &lt;strong&gt;2018&lt;/strong&gt; in Ranchi, Jharkhand by the Hon&amp;#39;ble Prime Minister of India, Shri Narendra Modi.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;P.M. Vaya Vandan Yojana&lt;/strong&gt;:
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The Pradhan Mantri Vaya Vandana Yojana was launched in &lt;strong&gt;2017&lt;/strong&gt; by the Ministry of Finance to offer a guaranteed payout of pension to senior citizens every month.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The Scheme can be bought offline as well as online through the Life Insurance Corporation (LIC) which has been given the sole privilege to operate this Scheme.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;P.M. Rojgar Protsahan Yojana&lt;/strong&gt;:
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: #000000;&quot;&gt;The scheme &amp;ldquo;Pradhan Mantri Rojgar Protsahan Yojana&amp;rdquo;(PMRPY) was announced in the Budget for &lt;strong&gt;2016-17&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: #000000;&quot;&gt;The objective of the scheme is to promote employment generation.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: #000000;&quot;&gt;The scheme is being implemented by the Ministry of Labour and Employment.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: #000000;&quot;&gt;The PMRPY scheme is targeted for workers earning wages upto Rs. 15,000/- per month.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Swachh Bharat Abhiyan&lt;/strong&gt;:
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Swachh Bharat Abhiyan is one of the most popular and significant missions in the History of India. This drive was introduced by the Prime Minister, Narendra Modi, and was launched on 2nd October &lt;strong&gt;2014&lt;/strong&gt; to honor Mahatma Gandhi&amp;rsquo;s vision of a Clean country.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The correct answer is - Hicks&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Hicks&lt;/strong&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;John Hicks introduced the LM curve as part of the IS-LM model, a fundamental tool in macroeconomics to analyze the interaction between the goods market (IS curve) and the money market (LM curve).&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The LM curve represents the equilibrium points in the money market, where the demand for money equals the supply of money at different interest rates and levels of income.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The IS-LM model was developed in Hicks&amp;#39;s seminal paper &amp;quot;Mr. Keynes and the Classics&amp;quot; (1937), where he formalized Keynesian economics into a graphical framework.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Hicks&amp;#39;s LM curve helps in understanding how monetary policy impacts interest rates and income levels, forming the basis for macroeconomic policy analysis.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Hausen&lt;/strong&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Hausen is not associated with the development of the LM curve or macroeconomic models.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;There is limited or no significant contribution from Hausen in the context of IS-LM analysis or Keynesian economics.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Friedman&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Milton Friedman was a prominent economist known for his contributions to monetarist theory, not Keynesian economics or the IS-LM model.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Friedman emphasized the role of monetary policy and developed the quantity theory of money but did not contribute to the LM curve specifically.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Tobin&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;James Tobin made significant contributions to macroeconomics, including portfolio theory and the Tobin&amp;#39;s q theory, but he did not develop the LM curve.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Tobin&amp;#39;s work often complemented Keynesian ideas but was distinct from Hicks&amp;#39;s IS-LM framework.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
